# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Parkno project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Package Management
**Created:**
- `package.json` - Added project configuration with @vercel/speed-insights v1.3.1 as a dependency

**Modified:**
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with the new dependency

### 2. Speed Insights Integration Script
**Created:**
- `scripts/speed-insights.js` - Vanilla JavaScript implementation that:
  - Initializes the Speed Insights queue (window.si)
  - Dynamically loads the Vercel Speed Insights script from `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js`
  - Includes proper error handling for content blockers
  - Sets appropriate SDK metadata (name and version)

### 3. HTML Pages Updated
Added `<script src="/scripts/speed-insights.js" defer></script>` to all HTML pages before the closing `</head>` tag:
- `healthz.html`
- `index.html`
- `login.html`
- `password.html`
- `poster.html`
- `register.html`
- `waitlist.html`

### 4. Security Headers Updated
**Modified:**
- `vercel.json` - Updated Content-Security-Policy to allow:
  - `script-src`: Added `https://va.vercel-scripts.com` for Speed Insights scripts
  - `connect-src`: Added `https://vitals.vercel-insights.com` for data transmission

- `_headers` - Updated with the same CSP changes for consistency

## Implementation Approach
This is a vanilla HTML/JavaScript project (not using a framework like Next.js or React), so I implemented the Speed Insights integration using:
1. The base `@vercel/speed-insights` package
2. A custom initialization script that follows Vercel's recommended approach for static sites
3. The script dynamically injects the Speed Insights tracking code, which will automatically collect Web Vitals data

## Why This Approach?
- **Framework-agnostic**: Works with plain HTML/JavaScript without requiring a build system
- **Performance**: Uses deferred loading to avoid blocking page rendering
- **Maintainable**: Single script file included across all pages
- **Secure**: Updated CSP headers to explicitly allow only necessary Speed Insights domains
- **Production-ready**: The script will only collect data in production (Vercel automatically handles this)

## Next Steps
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel Dashboard for this project
3. Speed Insights will automatically start collecting Web Vitals data from real user visits
4. View performance metrics in the Vercel Dashboard under the Speed Insights section

## Testing Notes
- Linter: No linter configured (returned success)
- Tests: No tests configured (returned success)
- All 7 HTML files successfully updated with the Speed Insights script
- Package installation completed without vulnerabilities
- CSP headers properly configured to allow Speed Insights domains

